p of yogurt a day drastically' b"reduces a woman's chances of getting vaginal candida, a yeast infection." b'for the year-long study, researchers at long island jewish medical' b'center in new hyde park, new york, recruited women who suffered from' b'chronic yeast infections. for the first months, the women each day ate' b'8 ounces of yogurt containing lactobacillus acidophilus. for the second' b'6 months, the women did not eat yogurt. the researchers examined the' b'women each month and found that incidents of colonization and infection' b'were significantly lower during the period when the women ate yogurt.' b'the fungus candida albicans can live in the body without doing harm.' b'it is an overproliferation of the fungus that leads to infection. the' b'researchers concluded that the l. acidophilus bacteria found in some' b'brands of yogurt retard overgrowth of the fungus. streptococcus' b'thermophilus and l. bulgaricus are the two bacteria most commonly used' b'in commercial yogurt production. neither one appears to exert a' b'protective effect against candida albicans, however. women who want to' b'try yogurt as a preventive measure should choose a brand that lists' b'acidophilus in its contents.' b'--- end b'' b'' b'' b'===================================' b'' b"infotrac health reference center oct oct b"the material contained in health reference center oct oct is provided" b'only for informational purposes and should not be construed as' b'medical advice or instruction. consult your health professional' b'for advice relating to a medical problem or condition.' b'' b'' b'heading: candida albicans' b'' b'1. candida (monilia). (infections caused by fungi)' b'(infectious diseases) by harold c. neu the columbia' b'univ. coll. of physicians surgeons complete home' b"medical guide edition p472(1)" b'text available' b'text' b'copyright crown publishers inc. b'candida (monilia)' b'this disease is usually caused by candida albicans, a fungus that we' b'all carry at one time or another. in some circumstances, though, the' b'organisms proliferate, producing symptomatic infection of the mouth,' b'intestines, vagina, or skin. when the mouth or vagina are infected, the' b'disease is commonly called thrush.' b'vaginitis caused by candida often afflicts women on birth control' b'pills or antibiotics. there is itching and a white, cheesy discharge.' b'among narcotic addicts, candida infections can lead to heart valve' b'inflammation.' b'diagnosis of candida infections is confirmed by cultures and blood' b'tests. treatment can be with amphotericin b or orally with ketoconazole.' b'there is no evidence that candida in the intestine of normal individuals' b'leads to disease. all people at one time or another have candida in' b'their intestines. claims for any benefit from special diets or chronic' b'antifungal agents is not based on any solid evidence.' b'--- end b'' b'' b'' b'==========================' b'i hope this is informative.' b'larry' b'' b'~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~' b"live from new york, it's saturday night..." b'' b"tonight's special guest:" b'~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~' 